The paper deals with the performance analysis of uplink cellular systems with delayed channel state information (CSI) and pilot contamination, which are both topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of zero-forcing decoder and the impact of user mobility on the system performance suggest that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and communication (cs.COMM). Finally, the paper provides asymptotic analysis results, which may be related to machine learning (cs.MA) techniques.
